blic classes. It's a bit of a puzzle figuring out the accessibility rules and constructor visibility!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic report needs**\\n\\nI'm thinking about possibly needing a dynamic access report in the build. Maybe I need to check if the existing report indicates anything that remains uncovered due to the current ReflectiveSchemaTest being too focused on outer layers. I might also need to consider the calcite dependencies for this. It looks like I need to write down what I discover to keep track of it all. Let's ensure everything is covered!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_K5jnlmIKmwaaNN21fya5k3FQ|fc_08354a2f032c5b6a016a2545c1f4788193a1a722c8262fb561", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/src/test/java/org_apache_calcite/calcite_core/ReflectiveSchemaInnerFactoryTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_calcite.calcite_core;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport org.apache.calcite.adapter.java.ReflectiveSchema;\nimport org.apache.calcite.schema.ScannableTable;\nimport org.apache.calcite.schema.Schema;\nimport org.apache.calcite.schema.Table;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ReflectiveSchemaInnerFactoryTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void createsReflectiveSchemaFromPublicNoArgumentConstructor() {\n        Schema schema = new ReflectiveSchema.Factory().create(null, \"catalog\", Map.of(\n                \"class\", ConstructorCatalog.class.getName()));\n\n        assertThat(schema.getTableNames()).contains(\"constructorRecords\");\n        Table table = schema.getTable(\"constructorRecords\");\n        assertThat(table).isInstanceOf(ScannableTable.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsReflectiveSchemaFromPublicStaticFactoryMethod() {\n        Schema schema = new ReflectiveSchema.Factory().create(null, \"catalog\", Map.of(\n                \"class\", StaticFactoryCatalog.class.getName(),\n                \"staticMethod\", \"create\"));\n\n        assertThat(schema.getTableNames()).contains(\"factoryRecords\");\n        Table table = schema.getTable(\"factoryRecords\");\n        assertThat(table).isInstanceOf(ScannableTable.class);\n    }\n\n    public static final class ConstructorCatalog {\n\n        public final List<CatalogRecord> constructorRecords = List.of(\n                new CatalogRecord(1, \"created with constructor\"));\n\n        public ConstructorCatalog() {\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class StaticFactoryCatalog {\n\n        public final List<CatalogRecord> factoryRecords = List.of(\n                new CatalogRecord(2, \"created with static factory\"));\n\n        private StaticFactoryCatalog() {\n        }\n\n        public static StaticFactoryCatalog create() {\n            return new StaticFactoryCatalog();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class CatalogRecord {\n\n        public final int id;\n        public final String description;\n\n        CatalogRecord(int id, String description) {\n            this.id = id;\n            this.description = description;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1145, "output": 1633, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17626, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780827557522, "responseId": "resp_08354a2f032c5b6a016a2545a5e1948193afc7d5496c577963"}}
